item.title: Ukraine not involved in drone attack on Moscow: Zelensky’s adviser
item.dc:creator: Balsakmaa
item.description: Ukraine has denied involvement in the drone attack in the Russian capital, Moscow. The attack […]
item.content:encoded:
Ukraine has denied involvement in the drone attack in the Russian capital, Moscow. The attack happened early Tuesday morning. However, no one was injured.

Mykhailo Podoliak, an adviser to Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky, denied the drone strike in Moscow in response to a question on a television program. He said, ‘We are not involved in any way.’

“This morning, a drone strike at sunrise caused minor damage to some buildings,” Moscow Mayor Sergei Sobyanin said shortly after the drone strike. City emergency services responded to the scene â€¦ No one was reported to be seriously injured.’

Moscow is more than 1000 kilometers away from Ukraine. Drone strikes in Moscow have been rare since the start of the Russia-Ukraine war. However, other parts of Russia are subject to almost regular drone strikes.

Pictures posted on social media showed smoke billowing from the site of the impact. The windows of some buildings were broken.
